    <section id="services" class="container">
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Our Key Services</h2>
            <p>We offer a range of environmental services, specializing in vegetation management, hazardous waste remediation, and civil construction. We help clients with projects like wildfire debris removal, stream restoration, and managing vegetation around critical infrastructure for utilities. We provide both engineering and construction services for public and private sector clients.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Vegetation Management:</strong> Controls overgrowth, reduces wildfire hazards, and maintains clearance for utilities through services like pre- and post-inspections.</li>
                <li><strong>Remediation and Cleanup:</strong> Cleans up contaminated land and water, handles hazardous waste, and removes debris following events like wildfires.</li>
                <li><strong>Construction:</strong> Includes civil construction, site preparation, and structural demolition.</li>
                <li><strong>Environmental Engineering:</strong> Provides technical assistance, project design, permitting, and consultation from project conception to completion.</li>
                <li><strong>Stream and Waterway Work:</strong> Engages in stream restoration and designs natural stream channels.</li>
                <li><strong>Tree Diagnosis and Treatment:</strong> Expert specialization in identifying and treating tree health issues, ensuring long-term vitality.</li>
                <li><strong>Municipal Contractual Services:</strong> Available for hire on contracts requiring an ISA Certified Arborist for municipalities, colonies, new construction, preservation, and more.</li>
                <li><strong>Regenerative Agriculture Consulting:</strong> Leveraging a bachelor's degree in regenerative agriculture and sustainability, we offer expert guidance on sustainable farming practices, soil health improvement, crop rotation, and ecosystem restoration to promote long-term land productivity and environmental health.</li>
                <li><strong>Sustainability Consulting:</strong> Providing comprehensive sustainability strategies, including senior project-based insights on eco-friendly initiatives, resource management, and sustainable development for municipal, agricultural, and construction projects in Michigan's exploding sustainability sector.</li>
                <li><strong>GIS and LiDAR Coming Soon:</strong> Expanding our capabilities with Geographic Information System (GIS) and Light Detection and Ranging (LiDAR) services for advanced environmental mapping, precision analysis, and data-driven decision-making. These tools will enhance our regenerative agriculture, sustainability, and tree management offerings, providing clients with high-resolution 3D terrain models, vegetation monitoring, and resource planning to optimize projects like urban forestry, land restoration, and infrastructure development. Stay tuned for launch details—contact us to learn more or pre-register interest!</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Serving all of Michigan with 24/7 availability – Call (248)941-1513 to discuss your project.</p>
